# Privacy and Data Handling Rules

- Treat this project as local-first and privacy-first by default.
- Do not introduce cloud LLM providers or external AI API dependencies unless explicitly requested.
- Keep GitHub tokens transient (in-memory per request), never persisted or logged.
- Avoid persisting commit data, standup content, or chat content unless explicitly requested.
- Do not assume a database layer; this project currently operates without persistent DB storage.
- Avoid adding telemetry, analytics, or background data collection by default.
- If a change impacts runtime config, call out required updates to `docker-compose.yml` and environment variables.
